64W.F.summary: CDON AB operates an e-commerce portal. It sells games, books, electronics, and music-DVDs through its website. The company was founded in 1998 and is based in Malmo, Sweden. CDON AB operates as a subsidiary of Qliro Group AB (publ.).

7B1.F.summary: BHG Group AB operates as a consumer e-commerce company in Europe. The company offers a range of brands totalling approximately 800,000 products within DIY, leisure, furniture, and furnishings. It operates approximately 85 online destinations comprising sites, such as www.bygghemma.se, www.trademax.se, www.chilli.se, and www.furniturebox.se, as well as approximately 70 showrooms. The company was formerly known as Bygghemma Group First AB (publ) and changed its name to BHG Group AB in May 2020. BHG Group AB was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Malmo, Sweden.

CD20.F.summary: Nelly Group AB (publ) provides digital commerce and related financial services in the Nordic region and internationally. It operates through three segments: CDON Marketplace, Nelly, and Qliro AB. The company's CDON Marketplace segment conducts operations through the online department store CDON.com, which primarily sells consumer electronics, mobile phones, books, games, media, films, sports and leisure goods, clothing, shoes, furnishings, and toys. Its Nelly segment provides fashion and beauty products for young women through Nelly.com; and for men through NLYMan.com. The company's Qliro Financial Services segment provides financial services to merchants and consumers. The company was formerly known as Qliro Group AB (publ) and changed its name to Nelly Group AB (publ) in November 2020. Nelly Group AB (publ) was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden.
